In order to help encourage some friendly rivalry in your challenge you can choose to enable several different leaderboards for teams and individuals. These will allow your users to keep track of their team's overall position, their individual progress and even create a leaderboard of their favourite teams.
Departments, locations or other 'segments' can also now compete against each other in their own unique leaderboards.
‍
Watch the video below to find out more.
When you set up your challenge you can choose to enable one leaderboard or all three, it's entirely up to you and what you think works best for your workplace.
Teams: Total Distance
‍
A list of all of your teams as well as their total distances.
Teams: Average Distance
This also displays all of your teams, but this time displays their average total based on the number of people on their team.
So a team of 3 can compete evenly against a team of 10.
Individuals: Total Distance
Instead of displaying all of the teams, this leaderboard shows all of the individual users from every team.
Yes!
Perhaps you wish to create some competition between teams in different locations, divisions or departments?
You can specify a list of segments when creating your challenge and each team will be required to select their appropriate segment. You can then display leaderboards based on those segments.
For example, you may wish to have all of the teams in the Finance division compete against the teams in the Communications division. Team segments allow you to do just that. Additionally, you can also allow all of the teams within the Finance division to run an internal competition amongst themselves.
All of our step challenges track your daily progress along a virtual route that stops off at interesting and unusual milestones along the way.
We've had a great response from our users explaining how much they enjoy learning about somewhere new around the world, all while they get out their daily exercise.
View our virtual walking routes
With our two challenge modes 'Teams Vs Teams' or 'One Big Challenge', you can choose to set up your step challenge so that each team is either competing against each other, or working together to combine all of their steps.
Teams Vs Teams
(most popular)
Our most popular mode and the easiest to set up; Teams vs Teams allows your participants to get into smaller teams and compete against each other on a leaderboard. This mode is a fun way to build some friendly competition and inspire daily physical activity.
One Big Challenge
All of your participants still get into teams, but now every team's total is pooled together to move everyone along the virtual map at the same time. This is a great way of seeing more of the world as you can cover much greater distances together!
Read more about our challenge modes:
